Introduction to Ceramic Tiles
Ceramic tiles have long been a staple in the construction and interior design industry, offering durability, aesthetic appeal, and functionality. These tiles, crafted from natural clay and other materials, are kiln-fired to achieve a hard, durable surface suitable for various applications in residential, commercial, and industrial settings.
Definition of Ceramic Tiles
Ceramic tiles are thin slabs primarily made from clay, minerals, and water. They are shaped, glazed, and fired at high temperatures to create a robust and moisture-resistant surface. Ceramic tiles are available in various designs, sizes, and finishes, making them a versatile choice for flooring, walls, countertops, and decorative purposes.
